# Adaptive AI Interview Assistant вЂ” Implementation Plan

## Architecture Analysis

### Image 1: System Architecture

The architecture shows a **6-module pipeline**:

#### 2.1 вЂ” Interview Question Engine
- Question Retrieval, Contextual Filtering, Difficulty Control
- Diversity Ensuring, Question Formatting
- Backed by a database of topic categories (DSA, System Design, OOP, DBMS, OS Networks, Behavioral, Domain Specific)

#### 2.2 вЂ” Multimodal Answer Understanding Module
- **Encoders**: Text Encoder, Speech Encoder, Vision Encoder
- **Fusion**: Adaptive Multimodal Fusion + Cross-modal Attention
- **Analysis Components**:
  - Semantic Understanding, Technical Correctness, Reasoning Quality, Explanation Depth
  - Code Quality, Communication Skills, Confidence Detection, Sentiment & Tone
- Outputs a **Unified Answer Representation**

#### 2.3 вЂ” Dynamic Competency Modeling Engine
- Updates Competency Graph в†’ Skill Graph в†’ Knowledge State Estimator в†’ Competency Confidence в†’ Updated Candidate Model

#### 2.4 вЂ” Adaptive Question Selection Engine
- Competency Gap Analysis в†’ Topic Prioritization, Difficulty Adaptation, Information Gain Estimation
- Candidate Profiling (Strengths, Weaknesses, Preferences)
- Question Scoring & Ranking в†’ Optimal Next Question

#### 2.5 вЂ” Current Confidence Gate
- Decision: "Enough" (end interview, generate report) vs "Not Enough" (continue)

#### 2.6 вЂ” Next Question Generation
- Retrieval-based Selection + LLM-based Question Generation (context-aware, adaptive)

#### 3. Output Layer
- Comprehensive Candidate Report: Interview Report, Competency Graph, Strengths, Weaknesses, Learning Recommendations

---

### Image 2: Implementation Pathway (Text/Code Focus)

| Step | Implementation | Learning Concepts |
|------|---------------|-------------------|
| 1 | Setup Foundation: Chat UI, Question DB, Basic Retrieval | FastAPI, SQL/NoSQL, Vector DBs |
| 2 | Answer Processing: LLM Evaluator, Metrics (Correctness, Reasoning, Code Quality) | LLM Prompting, Text Embeddings, Semantic Similarity |
| 3 | Dynamic Modeling: Skill Graph updates, Knowledge State, Skill Confidence | NetworkX, Bayesian Knowledge Tracing |
| 4 | Adaptive Question Selection: Skill gaps, RAG, routing | RAG principles, Adaptive Routing |
| 5 | Feedback & Output: Termination logic, Report Summarization | LLM Summarization, Data Serialization |

